# Commits and Workflow

## Commit messages — conventional commits

`type(scope): description`

Types: `feat` `fix` `docs` `style` `refactor` `test` `chore` `perf` `ci` `build`

## Granular commits

Commit small, cohesive changesets. Always use `git add .`. Push after each commit.

## Type checks before committing

Run `npm run type-check` from the project root before committing.

## .gitignore

When adding new apps, packages, or workspaces, add a thoughtful `.gitignore`.
